This paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on description logics, which is a subfield of logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the implementation of the subsumption algorithm in a knowledge representation system, which involves database management (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper introduces a new semantics for descriptions, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.DL).
